  "lyrics": "Wondering down in my bones Every time a little twist echoes A laughter whispers of more dreams They're in my rear view Wandering down these back roads Memories linger like a ghost Every turn a twist A reminder of what I miss the most Echoes of laughter, whispers of old dreams In the rear view mirror they're not as close as they seem Regrets a heavy load, a burden on my soul Every step I've taken, every path I've chose Regrets a heavy load, and a burden on my soul On these back roads of regret I'm searching for a sign A way to turn back time to the days when you were mine But the miles stretch out ahead There's no going back to where we've been Lost in this maze of memories I just keep being haunted by what we could've been So the sun sets behind me, casting shadows on the road Fading like the yesterdays, the stories left untold As each mile marker passes Like pages in a book of chapter closed I need every second look to tell me if I was right If you were wrong As each mile marker passes Like pages in a book of chapter closed Forever Regrets a haunting tune, a melody of pain Echoing in sounds, driving me insane On these back roads of regret I'm searching for a sign I've traveled down these roads with a heavy heart to bear Regretting every moment, wishing you were here I've traveled down these roads with a heavy heart to bear Wishing you were here Regretting every moment that leads me further away from where we were And what we needed to be Cause on these back roads of regret I'm searching for a sign A way to turn back time to the days when you were mine But the miles stretch out ahead There's no going back But the miles stretch out ahead There's no going back",
  "lyricsSegments": [
    {
      "end": 15.199999809265137,
      "text": "Wondering down in my bones",
      "start": 7.820000171661377
    },
    {
      "end": 22.3799991607666,
      "text": "Every time a little twist echoes",
      "start": 17.780000686645508
    },
    {
      "end": 25.639999389648438,
      "text": "A laughter whispers of more dreams",
      "start": 22.3799991607666
    },
    {
      "end": 28.920000076293945,
      "text": "They're in my rear view",
      "start": 25.639999389648438
    },
    {
      "end": 34.68000030517578,
      "text": "Wandering down these back roads",
      "start": 31.34000015258789
    },
    {
      "end": 38.2599983215332,
      "text": "Memories linger like a ghost",
      "start": 34.68000030517578
    },
    {
      "end": 41.7400016784668,
      "text": "Every turn a twist",
      "start": 39.040000915527344
    },
    {
      "end": 46.439998626708984,
      "text": "A reminder of what I miss the most",
      "start": 41.7400016784668
    },
    {
      "end": 51.08000183105469,
      "text": "Echoes of laughter, whispers of old dreams",
      "start": 46.63999938964844
    },
    {
      "end": 55.7599983215332,
      "text": "In the rear view mirror they're not as close as they seem",
      "start": 51.08000183105469
    },
    {
      "end": 61.41999816894531,
      "text": "Regrets a heavy load, a burden on my soul",
      "start": 55.7599983215332
    },
    {
      "end": 70.0999984741211,
      "text": "Every step I've taken, every path I've chose",
      "start": 62.380001068115234
    },
    {
      "end": 77.12000274658203,
      "text": "Regrets a heavy load, and a burden on my soul",
      "start": 70.0999984741211
    },
    {
      "end": 81.37999725341797,
      "text": "On these back roads of regret",
      "start": 78.12000274658203
    },
    {
      "end": 85.16000366210938,
      "text": "I'm searching for a sign",
      "start": 81.37999725341797
    },
    {
      "end": 92.23999786376953,
      "text": "A way to turn back time to the days when you were mine",
      "start": 85.16000366210938
    },
    {
      "end": 96.12000274658203,
      "text": "But the miles stretch out ahead",
      "start": 93.12000274658203
    },
    {
      "end": 101.04000091552734,
      "text": "There's no going back to where we've been",
      "start": 96.73999786376953
    },
    {
      "end": 104.44000244140625,
      "text": "Lost in this maze of memories",
      "start": 101.04000091552734
    },
    {
      "end": 109.22000122070312,
      "text": "I just keep being haunted by what we could've been",
      "start": 104.44000244140625
    },
    {
      "end": 113.91999816894531,
      "text": "So the sun sets behind me, casting shadows on the road",
      "start": 109.22000122070312
    },
    {
      "end": 117.83999633789062,
      "text": "Fading like the yesterdays, the stories left untold",
      "start": 113.91999816894531
    },
    {
      "end": 120.69999694824219,
      "text": "As each mile marker passes",
      "start": 117.83999633789062
    },
    {
      "end": 124.30000305175781,
      "text": "Like pages in a book of chapter closed",
      "start": 120.83999633789062
    },
    {
      "end": 129.86000061035156,
      "text": "I need every second look to tell me if I was right",
      "start": 124.45999908447266
